723777f-a.text:
Vermilyea Avenue, west side, north from Academy Street, showing school children out at recess time.
The apartment building on the N.W. corner was erected between 1918 and 1922.  66 and 72 Vermileay Avenue, the two buildings in the middle of the block, are a little older.
October 26, 1927.
P.L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
